n and France, European cultural history, and historical method.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aEurope. 4aGeneral. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh1 aJones, Colin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWahrman, Dror, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052022967940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092735340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927353423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927353/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles